   <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="discussion">
      <p>
Remarks
</p>
      <p>
Sabatinelli (1983)
described 
<tp:taxon-name>
Neodontocnema brancuccii
</tp:taxon-name>
ignoring the papers of 
Chang (1964)
and 
Nomura (1977)
in which 
<tp:taxon-name>
Neodontocnema
</tp:taxon-name>
was synonymized with 
<tp:taxon-name>
Miridiba
</tp:taxon-name>
. Later, 
Smetana &amp; Král (2006)
transferred this species to 
<tp:taxon-name>
Miridiba
</tp:taxon-name>
, which was confirmed by 
Bezděk (2016)
. According to the original description based on a unique male specimen, features of male genitalia such as parameres with two dorsal and two ventral branches (
Sabatinelli 1983
: figs 1–2) characterize to morphotype I “ 
<tp:taxon-name>
Trichophora
</tp:taxon-name>
”. Hence, this species is included in this genital morphotype.
</p>
